This paper discusses the use of chatbots as intelligent agents that engage in task-oriented or informal conversation. It also explores the issues related to learning, reasoning, representation, and execution for goal-directed autonomy. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of multi-modal conversation systems, which could fall under cs.LG (Learning) and cs.SD (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper discusses the Water Advisor system, which involves accessing and explaining sensor data, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering).
